title: Malaysia Three Month Interbank Rate
description: Malaysia Three Month Interbank Rate was at 3.46 percent on Wednesday November 9. Interbank Rate in Malaysia averaged 3.87 percent from 1993 until 2022, reaching an all time high of 14.50 percent in July of 1997 and a record low of 1.93 percent in December of 2020. In Malaysia, the interbank rate is the rate of interest charged on short-term loans made between banks. This page provides - Malaysia Three Month Interbank Rate - actual values, historical data, forecast, chart, statistics, economic calendar and news.
